          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Why I Recommend AISQ Over Doing It Yourself",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I spent years taking manual meeting notes. I tried recording calls and re-listening. I tried shared Google Docs where everyone types simultaneously (chaos). I tried assigning rotating \"note-taker\" duties (nobody likes being the note-taker).",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Every manual approach has the same fundamental problem: it pulls attention away from the actual conversation. You're either missing details because you're writing, or you're fully present but leaving with nothing documented.",
